text: Arne Torolf Strøm. Arne Torolf Strøm (1 October 1901 - 2 April 1972) was a Norwegian politician for the Labour Party. He was born in Oslo. He was elected to the Norwegian Parliament from Akershus in 1945, and was re-elected on three occasions. ==References== * Category:1901 births Category:1972 deaths Category:Labour Party (Norway) politicians Category:Members of the Storting Category:20th-century Norwegian politicians
